Saudi Arabia  has invested more than
40 billion riyals ($11 billion) to expand agricultural and
livestock production outside the kingdom,  al-Watan  reported,
citing Eid al-Maâ€™arik, chairman of the agricultural investment
committee at the  Saudi Council of Chambers .  Most of the investments were made in the Ukraine, Brazil,
Argentina and Canada, the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
